Clean facilities and very polite, attentive staff.  Small menu but plenty to keep you sated while enjoying a craft cocktail.  Options to be seated at a table, at the bar, or lounge comfortably at the couches in the back.

I don't like throwing out 5 star reviews, but this place was amazing. Shishito peppers, the Frenchie sandwich, and the brown butter bourbon cocktail: all spectacular. Atmosphere was on point as well and service was polite and incredibly attentive. Such a good evening!
Everything is great about this place nice people nice conversations food and drink
Pony Up is my favorite place in Denver. The French Dips are the best in town (much better than Hillstone's) and the cocktails are fantastic.

If you like French dip sandwiches you will love this place. Probably one of the best French dip sandwiches I have ever had. The bread had a prefect crispy crunch to it and the roast beef was cooked to be tender enough to fall apart in your …
The French dip was marvelous. A good selection of scotch and beers

Great LoDo ambiance with a reimagined classic food offering.  The taste and flavor of their French Dips is phenomenal and dipping in french onion soup...life-changing.  The only inconsistency is that the physical ambiance and bar offerings …
Came in for happy hour a few days ago and we were helped out by Elaina who was awesome. We tried out some food and cocktails - everything was on point! Will definitely be back soon!
Great new place. Craft cocktails and French dip sandwiches. Friendly service and cool decor.

The french dip sandwich is the best french dip I've ever had, if the Chicago came in a hoagie I'd say the same, the fried potatoes are hands down the best I've had. I don't know where these people learned to cook their beef and Fri their …

Elaina was the most helpful waitress tonight- coming in hot with good drink suggestions!!! Not only was she friendly to our table, her drink wisdom was admirable. She made my first experience at Pony Up one to remember, which is awesome because it made me want to return!  Love the ambience and the food was so good!

Ordered delivery from here many times and I've been shocked at how incredibly delicious the Chicken Kara-age is. Not many places in Denver offer this japanese-style fried chicken and with such a delicious sauce and thin, crispy batter. Can't wait to have it again.

Had a tough time scoring this. Food is really good, freaking delicious. The server though, she was rude and really made the experience subtract those two stars. Worth a shot, but maybe do the take out and catch the attitude from your significant other instead of someone you have to tip.
Delicious menu. Friendly staff and a cool vibe for sure! Will definitely be back!
The Saigon French Dip has me addicted!

I have keep coming back for takeout over and over. The French Dip (and variations) are amazing and the pop ups are super cool. Grab a togo order or eat on the patio. Don't forget to donate  a meal to out of work service industry workers.
Service was as good as the food. Known for their french dips... And I give them a huge thumbs up. And then this chicken karaage.  Incredible.  Sat outside with a heater. Gotta support local.

cocktails were innovative. And they have these chocolate chip cookies that they sprinkle straight up CRACK on.
Absolute perfection! Service was too notched and the the food was superb, thank you to Sheamus and his entire staff.

Love patronizing this woman-owned business!  The ambiance is terrific, the French dip sandwiches are to die for and the cocktails are fantastic.  Now in the COVID era, this is one of the few restaurants I feel safe dining at - they're doing everything right!

The cocktails, the staff, the decor, the FRENCH ONION SOUP, the French dips, the owner, the pup paintings.. everything about this place is amazing. I find myself going there on the way home from work a lot and I couldn’t be happier with it!
Great menu. Nice place to hang out, as they seem to take sanitizing and social distancing very seriously. How can you go wrong with cocktails and french dips?

Stayed for a drink, no complaints
Good happy hour. My drink was really good. Also the French dip during lunch was SO good.

Limited menu but they were nicely able to accommodate our group of 18

Great spot with friendly bartenders and staff - custom drinks were made for us based on what we liked and the French dips were incredible! Will definitely be back.
Great dip, fries, and service!
Love Pony Up!

I saw an article in the in-flight magazine that mentioned this place, and it was only a 25 minute walk from my Airbnb. This place is amazing! OMG, get the sunsets and death cocktail and the Frenchie sandwich, you can't go wrong.
Get a Saigon dip

Just happened to be in Denver downtown wondering where to  grab lunch when a local suggested Pony Up for French dip sandwiches. Sandwiches were excellent, beef jus went well. Angela the owner is simply put a warming soul to be around. Thank you Angela for everything.

One of my new favorite bars in Denver. Fantastic atmosphere and wonderful drinks. Dylan is one cool cat.

The Frenchy sandwich is my favorite.  They also have a vegetarian sandwich as well as a few other sandwiches.   I would definitely recommend a visit.
Really good french dip sandwich...kinda pricey....but delicious.

Excellent service, friendly staff. We we're having happy hour drinks and the staff checked in on us just about perfectly.
I visited for a sandwich and a beer during happy hour, and the service was outstanding.  My server was friendly and attentive, the beer cold and delivered quickly, and the sandwich was incredible.

Incredible cocktails, great French dip sandwiches. Service was very good and the place wasn't crowded at all on a Saturday around noon. You've got to try the chicken karaage.

First time in Denver and I have never felt so at home. Chris is a wonderful bartender and the venue is amazing the look is and music is so on. Come here for a good time without the crowd.

So the menu is mostly french dips, the sandwich was pretty good.  It did cost $14 and didn't include any side or anything.  I strongly feel that the price should be a few dollars cheaper or include some sort of side to make it feel like a proper lunch.  The service was very attentive and overall a pleasant experience.

Incredible Saigon and phenomenal drinks and service. Love the atmosphere and staff!
